(1273, 1, '2012-04-19 07:17:37', '2012-04-19 07:17:37', '[travellermap type=HYBRID address="" latlang="34.1020145, -117.43563710000001" height=400 width=900 zoom=]\r\n<p style="text-align: left;" align="RIGHT"><strong>Researchers:</strong> Natalie Moore &amp; Brian Hanson</p>\r\n<strong>Synopsis:</strong>\r\n\r\nPollution and air quality are a growing concern among all Americans, especially in the San Bernardino area of Los Angeles, as we learned in various lectures, assigned readings, and movies this quarter. The average citizen’s voice may not make a huge difference in the debate, but that is why all American citizens rely on their elected officials to have a voice for them. However, Aquanetta Warren’s Political career has proved to be somewhat of a disservice to citizens concerned with this particular issue. The Fontana Herald newspaper articles over the last ten years has represented Aquanetta Warren as silent on matters relating to assigned search terms.\r\n\r\nShe shows a strong presence within her community. Although she wasn’t quoted in all of the articles we included in our excel data, she showed a strong presence within her community. The articles show the Aquanetta Warren attended fundraisers, health conferences and community events in an attempt to connect with her community.\r\n\r\nApart from advocating solar panels, she was somewhat silent in regards to the words in our search string. We were assigned to search the key phrases "air quality," "diesel," "pollution" &amp; "particulate". In the articles in the Fontana Herald News starting from 2002 through 2011, those exact phrases were rarely, if ever, mentioned. The only similar  findings\r\n\r\nShe is a very strong advocate for real estate redevelopment. When she became mayor in 2010, she protested the governors proposed ban on redevelopment firms. Aquanetta Warren’s ideal redevelopment of Fontana would bring pollution to the community. Although redevelopment can create green buildings and housing in the long run, during construction, air quality decreases and particulates increase from machinery.\r\n\r\nThe closest the mayor has ever come to mentioning air quality is her Healthy Citizens campaign. Overall, Aquanetta Warren has chosen what issues she wants to take a strong stance with, and issues involving air quality have not been her top priority. In the area of San Bernardino, air quality is deemed a very important to many of the citizens. Aquanetta Warren has not made these issues a detrimental concern. In over 150 articles, air quality was not mentioned once.\r\n\r\nTotal number of articles in which official is represented at least once as an attributed source: 45; time span between first and last attributed statement by your official (2-25-1995 to 4-11-2009).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Aquanetta Warren', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1248-revision-11', '', '', '2012-04-19 07:17:37', '2012-04-19 07:17:37', '', 1248, 'http://empirelogistics.org/uncategorized/1248-revision-11/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
