ice</a> (CCAEJ) is attempting to pressure local government to better regulate air quality in Mia Loma, which has some of the worst air pollution in the country.\r\n\r\nThe EL collective facilitates direct response to immediate social problems through accessible technology; the stimulation of a collective and participatory action that bypasses official media channels; and the forging of community and solidarity among related struggles.\r\n\r\nGroups are currently forming in the Bay Area, Los Angeles and Ohio. If you are interested in starting a group or joining the project as a researcher, contributor or collaborator, please <a href="http://empirelogistics.org/contact">contact us</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Contributors:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.warehouseworkersunited.org">Warehouse Workers United</a>\r\n<a href="http://intermedia135.ning.com/">University of California-Riverside students</a>\r\n<a href="http://classes.mwwilson.net/video-production/">Pitzer College students</a>\r\nArt Institute of California students\r\nCalifornia Polytechnic State University students\r\n<a href="http://www.warehouseworkersunited.org/">Sheheryar Kaoosji</a>\r\n<a href="http://kenrogers.org">Kenneth Rogers</a>\r\n<a href="http://cla.calpoly.edu/es_valle.html">Victor Valle</a>\r\n<a href="http://mwwilson.net">Michael W. Wilson</a>', 'ABOUT', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '696-revision-v1', '', '', '2012-08-29 22:34:07', '2012-08-29 22:34:07', '', 696, 'http://empirelogistics.org/uncategorized/696-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
