her, the adjacent ports are the fifth largest container port in the world.</em>\r\n\r\nThe Port of Los Angeles (POLA), located 20 miles south of downtown Los Angeles , is currently the largest container port in the U.S.\r\n<h3><strong>Economics of Port:</strong></h3>\r\n<h4><em>Rank in North American Container Volume by TEUs in 2013 (from AAPA): </em>#5</h4>\r\n<table width="398" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="bottom"><strong>Annual Container Throughput</strong></td>\r\n<td align="right" valign="bottom"><strong>2012</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Inbound Loaded TEU''s</td>\r\n<td align="right">4,092,621</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap">Outbound Loaded TEU''s</td>\r\n<td align="right">2,043,076</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Inbound Empty TEU''s</td>\r\n<td align="right">117,192</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Outbound Empty TEU''s</td>\r\n<td align="right">1,824,824</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign="top">Total</td>\r\n<td align="right">8,077,714</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nPort of Los Angeles <a href="http://www.portoflosangeles.org/">website</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Port of Los Angeles', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'port-of-los-angeles', '', '', '2013-11-20 06:34:01', '2013-11-20 06:34:01', '', 0, 'http://empire-logistics.org/?post_type=ait-dir-item&#038;p=2574', 0, 'ait-dir-item', '', 0),
