(2643, 1, '2013-11-21 03:20:25', '2013-11-21 03:20:25', 'Encompassing an area of 168 acres, the BNSF San Bernardino Railyard is located in a commercial and manufacturing area with several residential areas within 200 feet of the facility. This intermodal classification yard into two distinct sections referred to as the “A” yard and the “B” yard. The “A” yard consists of  a classification yard and a intermodal area where trains are primarily built, arranged for their particular destinations and refueled. The “B” yard is an automotive yard where automobiles are unloaded onto trucks for local deliveries, or where switching activity can take place as this portion of the yard also has a classification section.\r\nA recent air quality study shows unexpected levels of air pollution-related cancer risks associated with the BNSF San Bernardino Railyard. The Health Risk Assessment concluded that the potential cancer risk associated with the BNSF San Bernardino Railyard is about 500 in a million. Please refer to the HRA for more details.\r\n\r\n<em>(source: <a href="http://hydra.usc.edu/scehsc/web/resources/Map/Railyards/MiraLoma/Documents.htm">http://hydra.usc.edu/scehsc/web/resources/Map/Railyards/MiraLoma/Documents.htm</a>)</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>References:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://empirelogistics.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/bnsf_sb_final.pdf">Health Risk Assessment for the BNSF Railway San Bernardino Railyard</a>', 'BNSF San Bernardino Railyard', 'Encompassing an area of 168 acres, the BNSF San Bernardino Railyard is located in a commercial and manufacturing area with several residential areas within 200 feet of the facility. ', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bnsf-san-bernardino-railyard', '', '', '2013-11-21 03:22:42', '2013-11-21 03:22:42', '', 0, 'http://empire-logistics.org/?post_type=ait-dir-item&#038;p=2643', 0, 'ait-dir-item', '', 0),
(2665, 1, '2013-11-29 21:46:42', '2013-11-29 21:46:42', 'CITATIONS\r\n\r\nIssued on January 13, 2012:\r\n\r\nSummary of Penalties for <strong>Inspection Number 314757162\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Citation 1</strong>: General = $ 185.00 - "The employer''s procedures for identifying and evaluating work place hazards including scheduled periodic inspections to identify unsafe conditions and work practices is ineffective. The employer has not been effectively identifying unsafe work practices, procedures, and conditions."\r\n\r\n<strong>Citation 2:</strong> Serious = $ 4500.00 - "The employer has an emergency eyewash and shower unit located on the west side of the building for battery charging a1;1d maintenance. The eyewash and shower unit had been disconnected from the water source and did not shall supply potable water at the flow rates and time durations specified in ANSI Z358.1-1981 ."\r\n\r\n<strong>Citation 3:</strong> Serious = $ 4500.00 - "The employer failed to establish an authorized or safe speed for forklifts (industrial truck). On August 8th, 2011 a forklift operator employed by National Distribution Centers, LP was observed traveling at a high rate of speed and running a stop sign."\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Citation 4:</strong> Serious = $ 4500.00 - "The employer has an emergency eyewash and shower unit located on the west end of the building for battery charging and maintenance. The employer failed to flush the line and verify operation monthy. The inspection tag on,the emergency eyewash and shower unit had not''\r\nbeen checked or signed off since 2/09."\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>TOTAL PROPOSED PENALTIES</strong> = <strong>$13685.00</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://empirelogistics.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/NDC-NFI-Chino1-314757162.pdf">&lt;&lt;download the PDF of this OSHA citation summary&gt;&gt;</a>\r\n\r\nSITE INFO\r\n\r\nNFI (National Distribution Systems)\r\n\r\nSquare Footage: 1,001,000\r\nOffice Space: 11,827\r\nBuilding