(2693, 1, '2013-11-29 22:51:52', '2013-11-29 22:51:52', 'Located in the city of Mira Loma, California, the Union Pacific Mira Loma Railyard covers approximately 274 acres. The surrounding area consists of mostly industrial-commercial land, with the nearest residential area about 1,500 feet away. The Jurupa Valley High School  is located about 500 feet from the entrance of the railyard. This Union Pacific site include classification tracks, a gate complex for inbound and outbound truck traffic, loading and unloading tracks and a number of other facilities for locomotive operations.\r\n\r\n<em>(source: <a href="http://hydra.usc.edu/scehsc/web/resources/Map/Railyards/MiraLoma/Documents.htm">http://hydra.usc.edu/scehsc/web/resources/Map/Railyards/MiraLoma/Documents.htm</a>)</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>References:</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://ehp03.niehs.nih.gov/article/fetchArticle.action?articleURI=info%3Adoi%2F10.1289%2Fehp.10968">Traffic-Related Air Pollution and Asthma Onset in Children: A Prospective Cohort Study with Individual Exposure Measurement</a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://ehp03.niehs.nih.gov/article/info:doi/10.1289/ehp.7195">Lung Cancer in Railroad Workers Exposed to Diesel Exhaust</a>', 'Union-Pacific Mira Loma Trainyard', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'union-pacific-mira-loma-trainyard', '', '', '2013-11-29 22:51:52', '2013-11-29 22:51:52', '', 0, 'http://empire-logistics.org/?post_type=ait-dir-item&#038;p=2693', 0, 'ait-dir-item', '', 0),
